1
00:00:05,066 --> 00:00:06,653
Ever thought about being an actor?

2
00:00:06,653 --> 00:00:07,266
Huh?

3
00:00:07,866 --> 00:00:09,066
Oops, my bad.

4
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,300
Hey! Give back my wallet.

5
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:13,133
Does a table come free with the meal?

6
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:14,166
Mr. Hairy Guy.

7
00:00:15,266 --> 00:00:17,800
But soon, one of us is gonna be on TV.

8
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:20,866
No one’s going on TV next week.

9
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,000
Because we’ve actually got a gig.

10
00:00:25,366 --> 00:00:27,533
I'm so grateful to everyone lately.

11
00:00:27,966 --> 00:00:29,529
For giving it your all.

12
00:00:29,529 --> 00:00:31,933
And tomorrow, let’s fight together.

13
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:33,500
Let’s do this together.

14
00:00:34,866 --> 00:00:37,548
If you’re tired, just take a rest.

15
00:00:37,986 --> 00:00:42,704
Or just let me take care of you.

16
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:49,666
Did they just ghost us?

17
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,166
We've got everything ready.

18
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,772
So we’ve gotta keep going.

19
00:00:52,772 --> 00:00:53,272
Keep going.

20
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:57,324
Since we can't go to the audience, we'll bring them to us.

21
00:00:57,324 --> 00:00:59,020
We’re going live.

22
00:00:59,020 --> 00:01:00,852
A Likay performance on social media.

23
00:01:00,852 --> 00:01:01,666
For the first time ever.

24
00:01:02,266 --> 00:01:04,465
And if I ever make it onto TV,

25
00:01:05,122 --> 00:01:07,356
I'll make Petchprakai Likay Troupe

26
00:01:07,356 --> 00:01:10,198
famous across the entire country.

27
00:01:28,666 --> 00:01:29,907
Oh, P'Phet.

28
00:01:31,045 --> 00:01:33,047
I made green curry for you.

29
00:01:33,310 --> 00:01:34,245
So tomorrow,

30
00:01:34,507 --> 00:01:36,741
you can heat it up for Ping Pong Chae.

31
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:39,450
And...

32
00:01:40,544 --> 00:01:41,822
when’s Ploy back?

33
00:01:43,166 --> 00:01:45,026
Uh, I’m not sure.

34
00:01:45,245 --> 00:01:47,535
Back early if it’s a quick wrap.

35
00:01:47,535 --> 00:01:50,000
If it drags on, I’ll be late.

36
00:01:50,807 --> 00:01:52,304
Is something wrong, P'Phet?

37
00:01:54,668 --> 00:01:55,989
Good luck.

38
00:01:57,039 --> 00:01:59,375
I hope you get to do what you want.

39
00:02:01,166 --> 00:02:02,466
What I want?

40
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:06,200
And if I want to act in a series,

41
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,000
you’d let me go, wouldn’t you?

42
00:02:11,933 --> 00:02:14,333
If I ever get on TV one day,

43
00:02:15,266 --> 00:02:17,366
will more people know Petchprakai?

44
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:22,700
And is that what you want, Ploy?

45
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,799
I’m going for it.

46
00:02:25,149 --> 00:02:26,675
And I'm gonna make it happen.

47
00:02:27,857 --> 00:02:29,618
And if I ever make it onto TV,

48
00:02:30,537 --> 00:02:32,803
I'll make Petchprakai Likay Troupe

49
00:02:32,803 --> 00:02:35,594
famous all over the country.

50
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:13,010
Now we're in Bangkok, I'm counting on you.

51
00:04:13,798 --> 00:04:15,601
I’m heading to the casting.

52
00:04:16,170 --> 00:04:18,949
You guys get what P'Phet ordered.

53
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:20,668
Guy.

54
00:04:20,974 --> 00:04:22,805
Get the fabrics and items

55
00:04:22,805 --> 00:04:24,472
P'Phet ordered.

56
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:26,325
And Pleng,

57
00:04:26,325 --> 00:04:28,196
you check out the live gear

58
00:04:28,196 --> 00:04:29,429
and the sound system.

59
00:04:29,735 --> 00:04:32,300
Stick to the specs P'Phet approved.

60
00:04:32,866 --> 00:04:34,100
Don't mess it up, got it?

61
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:35,100
Got it.

62
00:04:36,366 --> 00:04:37,827
The three of us

63
00:04:37,827 --> 00:04:39,490
will split up.

64
00:04:39,490 --> 00:04:41,923
Then meet at the hotel this evening.

65
00:04:41,923 --> 00:04:42,423
Okay.

66
00:04:45,566 --> 00:04:46,366
Split up?

67
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:48,100
Why do we have to?

68
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:49,697
I mean...

69
00:04:50,704 --> 00:04:52,133
Pleng could just go with Guy, right?

70
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:56,733
It'll only take a second to grab things.

71
00:04:57,533 --> 00:04:59,346
And why would you go together?

72
00:04:59,346 --> 00:05:02,700
Isn't it faster if we split up?

73
00:05:02,933 --> 00:05:03,895
No way.

74
00:05:05,077 --> 00:05:07,532
Just in case someone sneaks off.

75
00:05:07,532 --> 00:05:08,500
Who are you talking about?

76
00:05:09,466 --> 00:05:10,266
No one.

77
00:05:12,366 --> 00:05:13,311
Listen, Pleng.

78
00:05:13,574 --> 00:05:16,128
Are you afraid Guy will sneak off,

79
00:05:16,828 --> 00:05:18,411
or...

80
00:05:18,674 --> 00:05:19,971
are you just afraid of getting lost?

81
00:05:19,971 --> 00:05:22,643
You’re going to Fortune. Even know how?

82
00:05:22,643 --> 00:05:25,466
You have to take the MRT. Ever used it?

83
00:05:25,466 --> 00:05:29,369
Need Guy to show you how?

84
00:05:32,166 --> 00:05:33,266
I can handle it.

85
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:35,300
Please, Bangkok?

86
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:36,600
It's a piece of cake.

87
00:05:36,933 --> 00:05:38,400
Could do it with my eyes closed.

88
00:05:38,966 --> 00:05:40,800
This is nothing.

89
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:42,100
Huh.

90
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:45,966
Okay then.

91
00:05:46,466 --> 00:05:48,100
Then let’s split up as planned.

92
00:05:49,366 --> 00:05:51,600
Get lost, get roasted.

93
00:05:57,466 --> 00:05:59,666
Petchprakai is taking over Bangkok!

94
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:01,041
Let’s go.

95
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,800
Why is it so quiet today?

96
00:06:33,566 --> 00:06:37,266
Yeah, you could hear a pin drop.

97
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,400
They all went to Bangkok.

98
00:06:41,766 --> 00:06:42,566
To Bangkok?

99
00:06:43,666 --> 00:06:45,900
Oh, for Guy’s casting?

100
00:06:48,866 --> 00:06:51,966
I mean P'Ploy’s casting, you guys.

101
00:06:54,366 --> 00:06:57,369
If she gets a role, will she come back?

102
00:06:57,369 --> 00:06:58,566
Or will they keep her there?

103
00:06:58,766 --> 00:07:01,500
She'll be back. She's an actor, not a scammer.

104
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:02,828
Right.

105
00:07:02,828 --> 00:07:06,162
Even if P'Ploy becomes a superstar, she'll return.

106
00:07:06,162 --> 00:07:07,533
Because she once promised...

107
00:07:07,966 --> 00:07:10,333
to make Petchprakai famous nationwide.

108
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:11,933
Really?

109
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,466
Bangkok is just so comfy.

110
00:07:14,066 --> 00:07:15,133
Why would she come back?

111
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:16,533
Hey!

112
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,400
She'll be back.

113
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,203
Her heart’s right here.

114
00:07:19,203 --> 00:07:19,746
Yeah.

115
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:21,200
She has to.

116
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:22,300
You think so?

117
00:07:22,566 --> 00:07:23,066
Yeah.

118
00:07:23,066 --> 00:07:23,566
She'll be back.

119
00:07:24,066 --> 00:07:24,866
She promised.

120
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:26,800
Wanna play football?

121
00:07:27,133 --> 00:07:27,933
Play football where?

122
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:28,800
Let’s go.

123
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,600
Go.

124
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:30,666
Let’s do it.

125
00:09:25,366 --> 00:09:26,321
Hello.

126
00:09:26,321 --> 00:09:28,285
I'm a bit late.

127
00:09:29,073 --> 00:09:30,656
Can I still get a casting?

128
00:09:31,445 --> 00:09:32,925
Which one, kid?

129
00:09:33,366 --> 00:09:34,166
Oh...

130
00:09:36,066 --> 00:09:37,466
The BL series.

131
00:09:37,766 --> 00:09:38,566
That table over there.

132
00:09:39,566 --> 00:09:40,300
Okay.

133
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:41,866
Thank you.

134
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:45,733
Hello.

135
00:09:46,166 --> 00:09:47,366
Here for the casting.

136
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,400
Name?

137
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,400
Tor Prakai.

138
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,666
From Ayutthaya.

139
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,900
My agent sent me here today.

140
00:09:54,766 --> 00:09:56,066
I have proof.

141
00:09:57,533 --> 00:09:58,700
Sign here.

142
00:10:04,466 --> 00:10:06,800
Take the script and wait for your number.

143
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:07,800
Thank you so much.

144
00:10:07,866 --> 00:10:08,666
Thank you.

145
00:10:41,866 --> 00:10:42,666
I'm hungry.

146
00:10:48,066 --> 00:10:49,133
Hang in there, Guy.

147
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,000
You'll eat soon.

148
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:04,863
Hang in there, Guy.

149
00:11:11,966 --> 00:11:14,700
Shit, longer than Likay verses.

150
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:18,700
Do you know?

151
00:11:20,166 --> 00:11:21,937
You’re the one I’ve been searching for.

152
00:11:23,513 --> 00:11:25,399
You’re like rain in the dry season.

153
00:11:25,399 --> 00:11:27,189
Like a secret figure in a blind box.

154
00:11:27,189 --> 00:11:29,239
Like an ice cream truck in the jungle.

155
00:11:29,239 --> 00:11:31,445
Like pork crackling in chicken noodles.

156
00:11:31,445 --> 00:11:32,366
What the hell is this?

157
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,893
Do you know?

158
00:11:39,781 --> 00:11:41,792
You’re the one I’ve been searching for.

159
00:11:42,011 --> 00:11:43,827
You’re like rain in the dry season.

160
00:11:43,827 --> 00:11:45,738
Like a secret figure in a blind box.

161
00:11:45,738 --> 00:11:48,156
Like an ice cream truck in the jungle.

162
00:11:48,156 --> 00:11:50,687
Speak up! Open your mouth.

163
00:11:52,166 --> 00:11:53,066
Scammie.

164
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:54,800
What’s up, Mr. Hairy Guy?

165
00:11:55,766 --> 00:11:56,466
Whoa.

166
00:11:56,466 --> 00:11:58,066
Mr. Hairy Guy again today?

167
00:11:58,733 --> 00:11:59,966
What are you doing here?

168
00:12:00,466 --> 00:12:01,256
Don't tell me...

169
00:12:01,606 --> 00:12:03,200
here to steal another wallet?

170
00:12:09,866 --> 00:12:10,896
Hey.

171
00:12:10,896 --> 00:12:11,600
Let’s see.

172
00:12:11,766 --> 00:12:13,466
Let me hear you read the script.

173
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,066
Number 33.

174
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:17,300
If you can't read it,

175
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:18,866
I won't let you pass.

176
00:12:19,466 --> 00:12:19,966
No.

177
00:12:19,966 --> 00:12:20,866
Give it back.

178
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:22,166
Hurry!

179
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:23,645
What the hell?

180
00:12:23,645 --> 00:12:24,566
Who could memorize this?

181
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:28,533
Something about rain in a blind box.

182
00:12:29,766 --> 00:12:30,357
Hey.

183
00:12:30,357 --> 00:12:31,776
Go practice it again.

184
00:12:31,776 --> 00:12:34,333
Or this BL will turn into a comedy.

185
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,228
Here.

186
00:12:49,228 --> 00:12:50,283
Eat something.

187
00:12:50,808 --> 00:12:53,020
You can't remember anything while hungry.

188
00:12:54,866 --> 00:12:55,666
Mm-hmm.

189
00:13:03,566 --> 00:13:04,771
Is it expired?

190
00:13:04,771 --> 00:13:05,533
Give it back then.

191
00:13:11,866 --> 00:13:12,666
Thanks.

192
00:13:15,566 --> 00:13:16,366
Mm-hmm.

193
00:13:16,733 --> 00:13:17,900
And what are you doing here?

194
00:13:18,133 --> 00:13:19,300
Casting too?

195
00:13:23,266 --> 00:13:24,466
Good luck then.

196
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,866
Mr. Hairy Guy, number 33.

197
00:13:31,166 --> 00:13:32,466
Mr. Hairy Guy, my ass.

198
00:13:33,049 --> 00:13:34,945
What a waste of time.

199
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,600
Number 30, you're up.

200
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:49,400
That's me.

201
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:52,933
Shit, P'Ploy!

202
00:14:02,124 --> 00:14:04,226
How'd it go? Fingers crossed.

203
00:14:04,226 --> 00:14:05,373
Good luck. Hurry back.

204
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:07,733
What I want?

205
00:14:09,566 --> 00:14:11,500
And if I want to be in a series,

206
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:14,300
you'd let me, right?

207
00:14:19,266 --> 00:14:21,766
But I won't come back to Likay.

208
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,966
Couldn't stop you anyway.

209
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,608
Really?

210
00:14:30,608 --> 00:14:34,300
Give it to me straight.

211
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:37,200
What?

212
00:14:38,066 --> 00:14:38,901
You know...

213
00:14:38,901 --> 00:14:41,133
For real. No lies.

214
00:14:42,566 --> 00:14:43,461
So?

215
00:14:43,811 --> 00:14:45,845
Really want me to act?

216
00:14:48,533 --> 00:14:49,359
Well...

217
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,333
I want you to do what you love.

218
00:14:55,616 --> 00:14:56,622
But then...

219
00:14:56,928 --> 00:14:58,735
I don't want you to go.

220
00:14:59,392 --> 00:15:00,824
I want you to stay with...

221
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,766
Petchprakai forever.

222
00:15:11,066 --> 00:15:12,832
I grew up with Petchprakai.

223
00:15:13,007 --> 00:15:15,741
Am I stuck here for life?

224
00:15:18,266 --> 00:15:19,066
I don't know.

225
00:15:19,666 --> 00:15:21,166
Bangkok's just too easy.

226
00:15:22,566 --> 00:15:23,566
Not like our home.

227
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:26,366
And everyone here is handsome,

228
00:15:26,733 --> 00:15:27,566
rich,

229
00:15:29,133 --> 00:15:29,933
and smooth-talking.

230
00:15:31,566 --> 00:15:32,733
Not like the guys here.

231
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:34,766
Jealous, are we?

232
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,171
I'm worried.

233
00:15:38,871 --> 00:15:40,328
And yeah, I'm jealous.

234
00:15:42,533 --> 00:15:44,500
I don't want you with the wrong crowd.

235
00:15:47,533 --> 00:15:49,050
I promise.

236
00:15:49,050 --> 00:15:51,627
I'll take care of myself.

237
00:15:52,371 --> 00:15:54,299
Won't be blinded by the lights.

238
00:15:55,218 --> 00:15:57,148
Won't listen to smooth talkers.

239
00:15:58,724 --> 00:15:59,810
Because...

240
00:16:00,666 --> 00:16:02,800
Got a stubborn man waiting at home.

241
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:05,500
Who?

242
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:07,866
No idea.

243
00:16:13,933 --> 00:16:16,533
Let the future wait.

244
00:16:18,466 --> 00:16:20,100
Let's just do our best today.

245
00:16:22,366 --> 00:16:23,600
Like this green curry...

246
00:16:24,466 --> 00:16:25,266
Is it good?

247
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:27,216
Taste this.

248
00:16:30,500 --> 00:16:31,766
Want the whole bowl?

249
00:16:32,666 --> 00:16:33,617
Something like that.

250
00:16:38,781 --> 00:16:39,456
Well?

251
00:16:40,682 --> 00:16:41,582
Salty.

252
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:44,732
You're lying.

253
00:16:44,732 --> 00:16:47,066
Spent all day on this. No way.

254
00:16:54,551 --> 00:16:55,320
Seriously, it's salty.

255
00:16:57,733 --> 00:16:58,533
Man.

256
00:16:58,666 --> 00:17:01,200
I'll water it down.

257
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:02,500
Are you for real?

258
00:17:02,829 --> 00:17:05,023
It's already boiling.

259
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:22,466
Shit!

260
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:34,700
Hello.

261
00:17:35,766 --> 00:17:38,133
Introduce yourself when you're ready.

262
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:42,261
Hi, I'm Ploy Ying.

263
00:17:42,524 --> 00:17:44,466
I'm a Likay heroine.

264
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,400
Why are you here for a casting?

265
00:17:48,566 --> 00:17:50,466
Wanted something new.

266
00:17:52,866 --> 00:17:54,750
How do you think a series

267
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:56,526
compared to Likay

268
00:17:56,526 --> 00:17:57,700
is different?

269
00:17:58,766 --> 00:18:01,088
Well, I think they're similar.

270
00:18:01,263 --> 00:18:05,327
It's all storytelling anyway.

271
00:18:06,115 --> 00:18:09,755
Making the audience believe

272
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:11,625
and feel it with us.

273
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:14,699
But the difference is...

274
00:18:14,918 --> 00:18:17,047
the Likay stage I'm on

275
00:18:17,047 --> 00:18:19,300
only has a few dozen people.

276
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:23,250
But in a series,

277
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:25,878
there will be millions.

278
00:18:27,628 --> 00:18:28,798
So, I...

279
00:18:28,798 --> 00:18:31,258
I want to try it once.

280
00:18:31,258 --> 00:18:34,506
To reach millions.

281
00:18:35,338 --> 00:18:37,410
and have them feel it with me.

282
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:41,961
In that case,

283
00:18:41,961 --> 00:18:43,900
Can you perform for us?

284
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,900
Should I follow the script?

285
00:18:47,533 --> 00:18:48,333
Uh...

286
00:18:49,366 --> 00:18:50,427
I'd like to...

287
00:18:50,427 --> 00:18:51,200
tweak it a little.

288
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,000
Go ahead.

289
00:18:54,795 --> 00:18:59,561
♪ Since our first sight ♪

290
00:19:01,049 --> 00:19:04,735
♪ I knew right then ♪

291
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:10,000
♪ You are the one ♪

292
00:19:11,168 --> 00:19:13,868
♪ I've waited for ♪

293
00:19:42,466 --> 00:19:43,817
Thank you very much.

294
00:19:43,817 --> 00:19:45,600
Our team will be in touch.

295
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:47,900
Thank you.

296
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:50,466
Do you know?

297
00:19:52,766 --> 00:19:54,600
You're the one I've been searching for.

298
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,400
You're like rain in the dry season.

299
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:02,766
Like a secret figure in a blind box.

300
00:20:04,533 --> 00:20:06,744
Like an ice cream truck in the jungle.

301
00:20:07,225 --> 00:20:10,214
Like pork crackling in chicken noodles.

302
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:17,900
Number 33 next, please.

303
00:20:19,900 --> 00:20:20,700
Right here!

304
00:20:28,133 --> 00:20:28,933
Holy crap!

305
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:31,533
Go in, go in.

306
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:33,133
Get in there.

307
00:20:43,100 --> 00:20:43,889
Hello.

308
00:20:43,889 --> 00:20:44,389
Wait...

309
00:20:45,066 --> 00:20:46,000
Scammie.

310
00:20:46,566 --> 00:20:47,366
Hey.

311
00:20:47,766 --> 00:20:49,666
Starting already?

312
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:51,866
No introduction?

313
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:57,819
Hello.

314
00:20:57,819 --> 00:20:59,575
I'm Tor Prakai.

315
00:20:59,575 --> 00:21:01,313
I'm 23 years old.

316
00:21:01,313 --> 00:21:03,049
I weigh 180...

317
00:21:03,049 --> 00:21:04,470
Wait, I mean...

318
00:21:05,739 --> 00:21:08,369
Weight 63, height 180.

319
00:21:08,933 --> 00:21:10,800
Did you memorize the script?

320
00:21:15,666 --> 00:21:16,466
Yes, I did.

321
00:21:17,166 --> 00:21:18,166
Let's see it then.

322
00:21:19,066 --> 00:21:22,266
Hey, for this guy...

323
00:21:23,100 --> 00:21:24,733
Let’s just ad-lib it.

324
00:21:25,066 --> 00:21:27,400
Since we're finding my acting partner,

325
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:29,800
instead of reading lines,

326
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:33,333
let's test our chemistry.

327
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:53,144
Then...

328
00:21:54,370 --> 00:21:56,142
how about a pleading scene?

329
00:21:59,866 --> 00:22:01,793
If you want my Gear,

330
00:22:02,318 --> 00:22:03,981
how would you ask for it?

331
00:22:04,287 --> 00:22:04,820
Let’s see.

332
00:22:05,170 --> 00:22:06,755
Show me what you've got.

333
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:12,385
Ready?

334
00:22:12,385 --> 00:22:15,266
Three, two, one, action!

335
00:22:19,066 --> 00:22:20,020
You.

336
00:22:20,414 --> 00:22:21,894
Got a Gear?

337
00:22:23,066 --> 00:22:25,766
If you do, give it to me.

338
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:36,966
Why should I?

339
00:22:40,366 --> 00:22:41,566
Because I want the Gear...

340
00:22:43,933 --> 00:22:45,000
and I want you.

341
00:23:02,066 --> 00:23:04,733
Excuse me, P'Ploy, number 30, right?

342
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:05,770
Yes, that's me.

343
00:23:05,770 --> 00:23:08,301
My boss wants to talk to you.

344
00:23:08,651 --> 00:23:11,226
He really loves Likay.

345
00:23:11,226 --> 00:23:13,522
You might get some good news.

346
00:23:14,733 --> 00:23:15,866
Sure, I'm free.

347
00:23:15,966 --> 00:23:17,572
This way, please.

348
00:23:17,572 --> 00:23:18,072
Okay.

349
00:23:23,366 --> 00:23:26,112
You know, right?

350
00:23:26,681 --> 00:23:28,912
How much this Gear matters to me.

351
00:23:29,087 --> 00:23:31,344
Why give it to a stranger?

352
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:33,600
Hello.

353
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:35,300
What do you mean, just met?

354
00:23:36,966 --> 00:23:38,300
We've met twice already.

355
00:23:39,566 --> 00:23:40,366
How cute.

356
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:41,533
How old are you?

357
00:23:41,933 --> 00:23:42,866
Twenty-five.

358
00:23:44,300 --> 00:23:45,533
Twice?

359
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,800
That’s barely knowing each other.

360
00:23:50,766 --> 00:23:52,733
What if we’re this close?

361
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,466
Still too far.

362
00:23:58,666 --> 00:23:59,215
Then...

363
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,422
what do I have to do

364
00:24:02,122 --> 00:24:03,669
to be close to you?

365
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:14,604
Good.

366
00:24:14,604 --> 00:24:17,700
Just like that. Don't let go yet.

367
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:32,066
I'll take my leave now.

368
00:24:49,533 --> 00:24:50,400
That's enough for now.

369
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,333
Maybe another day.

370
00:25:21,933 --> 00:25:22,895
Where are you going?

371
00:25:22,895 --> 00:25:23,666
I'll drop you off.

372
00:25:25,666 --> 00:25:26,466
No.

373
00:25:27,966 --> 00:25:28,766
I'm fine.

374
00:25:30,133 --> 00:25:31,333
Come on, let's go.

375
00:25:31,666 --> 00:25:34,066
Hey! What are you doing, Scammie?

376
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:37,753
Call me Scammie one more time,

377
00:25:37,753 --> 00:25:39,003
and I'll take all this stuff

378
00:25:39,003 --> 00:25:41,366
home with me, like a real scammer.

379
00:25:42,066 --> 00:25:42,900
Don't you dare.

380
00:25:45,066 --> 00:25:46,328
This belongs to my brother.

381
00:25:46,328 --> 00:25:47,826
It's crucial.

382
00:25:47,826 --> 00:25:50,700
Then where to?

383
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:52,901
Would you go to Mars?

384
00:25:52,901 --> 00:25:53,899
I would.

385
00:25:53,899 --> 00:25:54,399
Let's go.

386
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:55,966
Wait, you know the way?

387
00:25:56,866 --> 00:26:00,250
Mercury's home. It's on the way.

388
00:26:01,169 --> 00:26:01,816
Come on.

389
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:05,333
Here.

390
00:26:08,133 --> 00:26:08,933
Let's go.

391
00:26:09,466 --> 00:26:10,333
Just go.

392
00:26:13,966 --> 00:26:15,533
Crispy pork basil is ready.

393
00:26:16,366 --> 00:26:17,152
Thank you.

394
00:26:17,152 --> 00:26:17,652
You're welcome.

395
00:26:20,766 --> 00:26:22,866
Hey, that's mine.

396
00:26:23,866 --> 00:26:25,200
I ordered the same thing.

397
00:26:29,333 --> 00:26:30,900
Just kidding.

398
00:26:41,566 --> 00:26:42,366
Whoa.

399
00:26:43,100 --> 00:26:44,566
Starving, are we?

400
00:26:46,500 --> 00:26:47,866
I was at a casting.

401
00:26:49,066 --> 00:26:51,566
Haven't eaten all day?

402
00:26:52,566 --> 00:26:53,800
I was in a rush.

403
00:26:55,133 --> 00:26:56,975
It’s at noon. Overslept?

404
00:26:57,369 --> 00:26:59,533
Or busy shopping for this?

405
00:27:00,366 --> 00:27:02,500
Forget about me.

406
00:27:05,366 --> 00:27:06,466
You tell me.

407
00:27:06,733 --> 00:27:07,766
Who are you exactly?

408
00:27:09,766 --> 00:27:11,166
Why were you in that room?

409
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:17,300
And...

410
00:27:19,766 --> 00:27:22,546
Whoa, so handsome.

411
00:27:22,940 --> 00:27:24,416
He's a star!

412
00:27:24,854 --> 00:27:26,404
So fair!

413
00:27:27,666 --> 00:27:30,133
Why does everyone know you?

414
00:27:32,100 --> 00:27:36,300
I should be asking why you “don’t”

415
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,577
Don't tell me you're...

416
00:27:58,934 --> 00:28:00,000
Khun Thee?

417
00:28:01,133 --> 00:28:03,166
Thee Theeraphat here.

418
00:28:06,166 --> 00:28:07,500
Nice to meet you.

419
00:28:28,300 --> 00:28:29,333
Where is he?

420
00:28:39,700 --> 00:28:41,133
Where’s Guy?

421
00:28:42,133 --> 00:28:43,100
Oops, sorry!

422
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:45,900
Oh, P’Phet!

423
00:28:47,366 --> 00:28:48,166
Surprise!

424
00:28:51,466 --> 00:28:52,766
What are you doing here?

425
00:28:53,966 --> 00:28:55,400
Thought you were busy.

426
00:28:57,066 --> 00:28:59,133
I finished early.

427
00:28:59,900 --> 00:29:01,700
And needed more supplies.

428
00:29:02,866 --> 00:29:03,666
So...

429
00:29:06,966 --> 00:29:08,466
All the way here?

430
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:11,066
No markets near home?

431
00:29:12,566 --> 00:29:15,333
None of them have Ploy Ying.

432
00:29:21,495 --> 00:29:22,967
Oh.

433
00:29:23,886 --> 00:29:25,267
Or...

434
00:29:25,486 --> 00:29:28,100
Curious about the casting?

435
00:29:30,533 --> 00:29:31,413
No.

436
00:29:32,463 --> 00:29:33,790
I just...

437
00:29:35,366 --> 00:29:37,953
Maybe a little.

438
00:29:41,366 --> 00:29:42,967
I don't know yet.

439
00:29:42,967 --> 00:29:44,533
They'll be in touch.

440
00:29:46,133 --> 00:29:48,828
But the producer liked me.

441
00:29:49,091 --> 00:29:50,735
He called me in privately.

442
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:54,366
Man or woman?

443
00:29:56,366 --> 00:29:57,533
Jealous?

444
00:29:58,666 --> 00:30:01,416
Jealous? We aren't even a thing.

445
00:30:01,416 --> 00:30:02,533
Why would I be?

446
00:30:05,266 --> 00:30:06,933
Don't overthink it.

447
00:30:07,266 --> 00:30:08,766
Wait until I land the role.

448
00:30:09,566 --> 00:30:10,933
They might not even pick me.

449
00:30:11,333 --> 00:30:12,600
How could they not?

450
00:30:13,933 --> 00:30:15,363
Ploy Ying is beautiful...

451
00:30:15,363 --> 00:30:16,386
and talented.

452
00:30:16,386 --> 00:30:19,533
They'll cast you as an "Auntie."

453
00:30:19,900 --> 00:30:21,300
P’Phet!

454
00:30:22,366 --> 00:30:23,966
An "Auntie"? Looking like this?

455
00:30:24,666 --> 00:30:25,600
Just kidding.

456
00:30:28,166 --> 00:30:29,105
Anyway...

457
00:30:30,418 --> 00:30:31,678
Where are Guy and Pleng?

458
00:30:34,366 --> 00:30:35,991
Buying your stuff.

459
00:30:36,516 --> 00:30:37,812
Not back yet?

460
00:30:39,791 --> 00:30:40,766
Are they lost?

461
00:30:41,766 --> 00:30:43,500
I sent Guy with Pleng...

462
00:30:43,966 --> 00:30:44,966
so Pleng wouldn't get lost.

463
00:30:45,533 --> 00:30:47,166
Should be here soon.

464
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:55,766
Hello!

465
00:30:57,066 --> 00:30:57,866
P’Ploy!

466
00:30:58,566 --> 00:30:59,300
Next time,

467
00:30:59,300 --> 00:31:01,000
Just give me the right pin.

468
00:31:01,666 --> 00:31:03,500
I'm beat from shopping.

469
00:31:03,933 --> 00:31:04,766
So many shops.

470
00:31:05,066 --> 00:31:06,066
Location's wrong too.

471
00:31:07,133 --> 00:31:08,939
Stuck at the MRT for sure.

472
00:31:11,766 --> 00:31:12,519
Oh!

473
00:31:12,519 --> 00:31:13,412
P’Phet!

474
00:31:14,287 --> 00:31:15,160
What's up

475
00:31:15,729 --> 00:31:16,533
What are you doing here?

476
00:31:19,733 --> 00:31:20,533
Right.

477
00:31:21,366 --> 00:31:22,566
Good thing you're here.

478
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:24,333
I've got something to tell you.

479
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:28,933
Before you start snitching...

480
00:31:30,466 --> 00:31:32,200
fix your own mess first.

481
00:31:45,666 --> 00:31:46,733
Which way is it?

482
00:31:50,933 --> 00:31:52,308
Hey, Uncle!

483
00:31:52,308 --> 00:31:56,066
Where’s the Tulip Hotel?

484
00:31:56,266 --> 00:31:58,600
Tulip Hotel? Hop in.

485
00:31:58,900 --> 00:32:00,300
Is it free, Uncle?

486
00:32:00,491 --> 00:32:03,191
Just 100 baht for you.

487
00:32:03,900 --> 00:32:04,733
A hundred?

488
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:08,266
It's so close! Why so pricey?

489
00:32:08,266 --> 00:32:09,766
Then go walk it.

490
00:32:12,733 --> 00:32:14,984
Look, Uncle. At least...

491
00:32:15,903 --> 00:32:18,141
just tell me. Left or right?

492
00:32:18,447 --> 00:32:21,201
Can't do it. Trade secret.

493
00:32:22,796 --> 00:32:24,019
A hundred for that?

494
00:32:24,019 --> 00:32:27,125
That's a scam, not a profession.

495
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:31,000
Here's ten baht. Tell me.

496
00:32:31,333 --> 00:32:31,948
Ten baht?

497
00:32:32,342 --> 00:32:34,600
leftover wallets pay more.

498
00:32:34,766 --> 00:32:36,700
See? A total scammie.

499
00:32:37,533 --> 00:32:39,666
What’s going on?

500
00:32:40,333 --> 00:32:43,366
Lynchee! How'd you get here?

501
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:45,200
The subway.

502
00:32:50,300 --> 00:32:51,500
The MRT.

503
00:32:52,733 --> 00:32:53,533
Oh.

504
00:32:55,500 --> 00:32:56,300
Uh...

505
00:32:56,733 --> 00:32:57,700
Don't tell me...

506
00:32:58,733 --> 00:33:00,333
you're going to the Tulip Hotel.

507
00:33:00,800 --> 00:33:02,066
Yeah. How'd you know?

508
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:05,003
See? Fifty baht each.

509
00:33:05,003 --> 00:33:05,900
Hop in. Uncle will take you.

510
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:08,831
Fifty? Uncle!

511
00:33:09,064 --> 00:33:11,266
It's right there.

512
00:33:11,733 --> 00:33:12,533
Jeez.

513
00:33:13,533 --> 00:33:15,800
Save the gas for your mother.

514
00:33:16,066 --> 00:33:16,866
Move it.

515
00:33:17,325 --> 00:33:18,358
City people...

516
00:33:22,466 --> 00:33:23,933
Almost got scammed.

517
00:33:25,703 --> 00:33:30,070
So which way to the hotel?

518
00:33:30,933 --> 00:33:31,733
Follow me.

519
00:33:32,400 --> 00:33:33,200
Come on.

520
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:39,500
Pleng, were you seriously lost?

521
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:42,800
Wasn't lost!

522
00:33:43,666 --> 00:33:44,868
Just a bit turned around.

523
00:33:45,043 --> 00:33:45,833
Sure.

524
00:33:46,009 --> 00:33:46,859
"Not lost"? Yeah, right.

525
00:33:47,225 --> 00:33:49,366
Lucky my dad's staying here too.

526
00:33:49,766 --> 00:33:50,610
Otherwise,

527
00:33:50,610 --> 00:33:52,800
you'd be lost for a week.

528
00:33:53,066 --> 00:33:53,866
Dramatic much?

529
00:33:54,166 --> 00:33:55,133
Who gets lost for seven days?

530
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:56,842
Last time,

531
00:33:56,842 --> 00:34:00,166
you vanished for a day. I almost called the cops.

532
00:34:00,666 --> 00:34:02,463
Oh, so this is the guy?

533
00:34:02,463 --> 00:34:04,160
The one my dad had to rescue?

534
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:05,333
You again?

535
00:34:08,666 --> 00:34:10,466
Definitely lost if I hadn't shown up.

536
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:13,166
Wait, where's Guy?

537
00:34:15,333 --> 00:34:17,014
I sent Guy with Pleng...

538
00:34:17,014 --> 00:34:18,193
so he wouldn't get lost.

539
00:34:18,193 --> 00:34:19,366
And you weren't together?

540
00:34:19,766 --> 00:34:20,734
There you go.

541
00:34:21,040 --> 00:34:22,989
Knew it was fishy.

542
00:34:23,602 --> 00:34:24,435
This morning,

543
00:34:24,785 --> 00:34:26,689
P’Ploy told me to split up with Guy.

544
00:34:30,166 --> 00:34:32,608
Guy went for the fabrics,

545
00:34:32,608 --> 00:34:35,478
and Pleng went for the live gear.

546
00:34:35,478 --> 00:34:36,695
We didn't need to be together.

547
00:34:37,089 --> 00:34:38,987
We could just split up.

548
00:34:38,987 --> 00:34:40,072
Going together is a waste of time.

549
00:34:40,072 --> 00:34:42,075
To get it done faster.

550
00:34:51,700 --> 00:34:52,500
Hello, Mother.

551
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:55,533
Did my brother pick up the fabrics yet?

552
00:34:57,666 --> 00:34:58,466
What's that?

553
00:34:58,966 --> 00:35:00,000
He picked them up this morning?

554
00:35:01,933 --> 00:35:03,100
Oh, okay.

555
00:35:03,333 --> 00:35:04,133
Thank you very much.

556
00:35:08,566 --> 00:35:10,066
He got them this morning.

557
00:35:11,133 --> 00:35:12,533
Then why isn't he back yet?

558
00:35:13,533 --> 00:35:14,333
Right.

559
00:35:14,700 --> 00:35:15,866
He’s still not back.

560
00:35:16,466 --> 00:35:18,533
But ask P’Ploy.

561
00:35:18,900 --> 00:35:20,600
I think she knows.

562
00:35:21,533 --> 00:35:22,333
Ask her.

563
00:35:31,966 --> 00:35:32,766
P’Phet.

564
00:35:46,366 --> 00:35:47,166
Where have you been?

565
00:35:49,166 --> 00:35:50,766
Picking up the fabrics.

566
00:35:54,300 --> 00:35:55,752
I called the shop.

567
00:35:55,752 --> 00:35:57,503
They said you picked them up this morning.

568
00:35:58,116 --> 00:35:59,501
So why just now?

569
00:36:00,464 --> 00:36:01,254
Where were you?

570
00:36:10,666 --> 00:36:11,766
I'll handle this.

571
00:36:13,133 --> 00:36:13,933
P’Ploy.

572
00:36:28,400 --> 00:36:29,800
Number 30 next, please.

573
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:31,600
That's me.

574
00:36:33,866 --> 00:36:35,266
Shit, P’Ploy!

575
00:36:39,333 --> 00:36:40,133
Shit!

576
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:46,166
How do I get close to you?

577
00:36:49,333 --> 00:36:50,366
I'll take my leave now.

578
00:36:50,766 --> 00:36:51,566
Hello.

579
00:36:56,933 --> 00:36:58,766
Come on, P’Phet.

580
00:36:59,510 --> 00:37:02,877
Guy’s tired. Let him rest first.

581
00:37:02,877 --> 00:37:04,678
Look at all the stuff he's carrying.

582
00:37:05,335 --> 00:37:06,870
He’s all sweaty. Tired, right?

583
00:37:07,900 --> 00:37:09,754
Just answer my question.

584
00:37:09,754 --> 00:37:11,166
That won't kill you.

585
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:12,300
Right.

586
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:13,796
Well, Guy?

587
00:37:14,978 --> 00:37:16,238
Where were you?

588
00:37:17,666 --> 00:37:19,500
Well...

589
00:37:22,133 --> 00:37:23,000
I went to see a friend.

590
00:37:23,533 --> 00:37:24,127
Mmm.

591
00:37:24,127 --> 00:37:24,800
A friend?

592
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:28,666
You have friends in Bangkok?

593
00:37:30,133 --> 00:37:30,933
Mmm.

594
00:37:31,366 --> 00:37:32,166
Yes, I do.

595
00:37:32,533 --> 00:37:33,466
How did you meet?

596
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:35,900
Uh...

597
00:37:37,466 --> 00:37:38,266
An app.

598
00:37:38,533 --> 00:37:39,333
What app?

599
00:37:40,500 --> 00:37:41,300
Don't tell me…

600
00:37:42,266 --> 00:37:43,886
it's Finder.

601
00:37:43,886 --> 00:37:44,386
Whoa!

602
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,733
Isn't that a dating app?

603
00:37:48,166 --> 00:37:48,966
So...

604
00:37:49,366 --> 00:37:50,400
are you seeing a friend,

605
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:52,566
or seeing a boyfriend?

606
00:37:53,533 --> 00:37:54,333
Huh?

607
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:57,400
Well?

608
00:37:59,266 --> 00:38:00,333
Where've you been?

609
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:02,000
Huh?

610
00:38:04,400 --> 00:38:05,200
Well...

611
00:38:11,733 --> 00:38:12,533
Hello.

612
00:38:22,100 --> 00:38:23,866
I'm Tor Prakai's boyfriend.

613
00:38:54,483 --> 00:38:55,550
P'Phet!

614
00:39:01,066 --> 00:39:03,100
You're dead.

615
00:39:03,933 --> 00:39:04,558
Huh.

616
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:07,466
P'Phet, P'Ploy, wait up!

617
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:10,566
Told you! He really has a boyfriend.

618
00:39:19,366 --> 00:39:23,949
How many showers do you take to look this good?

619
00:39:23,949 --> 00:39:25,949
So clean.

620
00:39:28,181 --> 00:39:31,337
How'd you find him, Tor Prakai?

621
00:39:31,994 --> 00:39:33,241
DM me and let me know.

622
00:39:37,500 --> 00:39:40,896
If you like this style...me too!

623
00:39:41,509 --> 00:39:44,598
Look, we're wearing the same print.

624
00:39:48,500 --> 00:39:50,500
Lynchee, let's go.

625
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:52,600
Hurry!

626
00:39:53,133 --> 00:39:54,733
Yeah, they're being serious.

627
00:39:56,933 --> 00:39:59,733
They need to talk it out.

628
00:40:01,566 --> 00:40:02,466
See you later!

629
00:40:07,666 --> 00:40:08,466
Hurry up!

630
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:18,066
What on earth are you doing?

631
00:40:38,501 --> 00:40:40,644
♪ My heart so fearful ♪

632
00:40:41,432 --> 00:40:43,207
♪ and so bold ♪

633
00:40:43,894 --> 00:40:45,333
♪ Longing to find ♪

634
00:40:46,077 --> 00:40:48,077
♪ my beloved ♪

635
00:40:49,084 --> 00:40:50,417
♪ my sweet one ♪

636
00:40:53,174 --> 00:40:54,786
♪ To be near you ♪

637
00:40:55,312 --> 00:40:57,668
♪ every second ♪

638
00:40:58,674 --> 00:41:01,900
♪ This very heart ♪

639
00:41:02,425 --> 00:41:04,600
♪ is calling out ♪

640
00:41:06,613 --> 00:41:09,620
♪ Desiring to be the one ♪

641
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:11,649
♪ to support ♪

642
00:41:13,093 --> 00:41:15,635
♪ you ♪

643
00:41:16,161 --> 00:41:17,943
♪ all the ♪

644
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:21,046
♪ time ♪

645
00:41:31,466 --> 00:41:35,533
Nine Theeraphat, the million-view actor.

646
00:41:35,866 --> 00:41:37,533
I mean “you”…have a superstar boyfriend?

647
00:41:38,866 --> 00:41:40,866
I already passed.

648
00:41:40,866 --> 00:41:41,383
Shit!

649
00:41:41,733 --> 00:41:45,166
You're so fishy. I'm watching you.

650
00:41:45,333 --> 00:41:46,600
No need to watch me.

651
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:48,933
Is being with Petchprakai that bad?

652
00:41:49,100 --> 00:41:50,333
After I gave you everything.

653
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:51,464
I taught you to sing and dance.

654
00:41:51,464 --> 00:41:53,622
To make you a great Likay hero.

655
00:41:53,622 --> 00:41:54,700
But I never wanted that.

656
00:41:55,366 --> 00:41:56,794
Did your boyfriend teach you this?
